Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "manji":

1. Ja imam manji auto od svog brata. (*manji*) (I have a smaller car than my brother.)
2. Njegova plata je manja od moje. (plata = salary) (His salary is smaller than mine.)
3. Treba nam manji sto za ovu sobu. (*manji*) (We need a smaller table for this room.)
4. Ona ima manje iskustva od mene. (iskustvo = experience) (She has less experience than me.)
5. Ovo je manji problem od onog s kojim smo se suočili juče. (*manji*) (This is a smaller problem than the one we faced yesterday.)
6. Hoćeš li manju ili veću porciju? (*manju*) (Do you want a smaller or a larger portion?)
7. On ima manje obaveza od nas. (obaveze = obligations) (He has fewer obligations than us.)
8. Kupili smo manju kuću u novom naselju. (*manju*) (We bought a smaller house in the new neighborhood.)
9. Potrebna mi je manja količina brašna za ovaj kolač. (*manja*) (I need a smaller amount of flour for this cake.)
10. Moj pas je manjeg rasta od tvog psa. (*manjeg*) (My dog is smaller in size than your dog.)

Note: The word "manji" in these sentences is in different forms (manji, manja, manje, manju, manjeg) depending on its gender, case, and function in the sentence.